      • tree

        public boolean tree
        Determines whether or not a node or an edge belongs to a tree. This attribute is essential for edges but optional for nodes. By default a node belongs to a tree if at least one of its adjacent edges is marked as a tree-edge. GraphWalkers normally use only the edge.tree attribute. But there may be some special Walkers (like TightTreeWalker) that use the node.tree as a redundant shortcut. In any other case the validity of this value is not guaranteed.
        However, if you don't plan to use the graph as a tree (e.g. using TreeWalkers) you don't need to care about this field.
